01:19:42.450 --> 01:19:44.600
Kate Sackton: What does the clock look like?

922
01:19:44.600 --> 01:19:53.070
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): is… immense. It is, easily six and a half or seven feet tall, solid.

923
01:19:53.400 --> 01:20:02.470
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): old, well-joined masterwork. There are… there is one dial,

924
01:20:03.720 --> 01:20:05.390
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): There are a number of things going on in the face of the clock.

925
01:20:05.390 --> 01:20:06.030
David S. Kong: One of the.

926
01:20:06.030 --> 01:20:08.240
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): is the dial. The dial…

927
01:20:08.460 --> 01:20:13.499
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Even though it's a circle, and it seems to be in the format of, like, the…

928
01:20:13.500 --> 01:20:14.400
David S. Kong: The number at the.

929
01:20:14.400 --> 01:20:26.680
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): top and the sides and the bottom is a little bit larger. It is not a 12- or a 24-hour face. From this distance, all you can see is that each of the dial positions has 4 digits.

930
01:20:26.830 --> 01:20:31.159
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And there are… Many more than 12 of them.

931
01:20:31.160 --> 01:20:31.610
David S. Kong: Oh, okay.

932
01:20:31.610 --> 01:20:32.849
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You'd have to get closer to see it.

933
01:20:32.850 --> 01:20:33.270
David S. Kong: No, no, no.

934
01:20:33.730 --> 01:20:35.939
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Then, below it, though.

935
01:20:35.940 --> 01:20:36.979
David S. Kong: You meant to answer it away.

936
01:20:36.980 --> 01:20:41.300
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): What is stranger still… is,

937
01:20:43.560 --> 01:20:52.670
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): There are 4 different smaller dials below it, each of which have a hand pointing to numbers too small to be read.

938
01:20:53.140 --> 01:21:09.880
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And then below each one of those dials, so here's your big dial at the top, and then here's your four ones in a row underneath it, underneath each of those, is what looks like 6 numbers, like a 6-digit number that's below each of those 4 faces.

939
01:21:10.870 --> 01:21:15.229
Mike Sackton: One six-digit number spread out, or six six-digit… four six-digit.

940
01:21:15.230 --> 01:21:19.709
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Four, yeah, four six-digit numbers, one below each one of the faces.

941
01:21:19.710 --> 01:21:24.439
Audio shared by David S. Kong: and you cannot…

942
01:21:24.550 --> 01:21:33.970
Audio shared by David S. Kong: You probably can't really read the numbers from this distance, this clock's probably 20 or 30 feet away, but you can tell that those numbers are changing.

943
01:21:34.490 --> 01:21:44.990
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Apparently at random. It's not like they're counting up or something successfully. But it's almost like little wheels of numbers, like an odometer on a car, and they're just like, flap, flap-flop-flop-flop.

944
01:21:45.240 --> 01:21:46.410
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Stay the same.

945
01:21:47.690 --> 01:21:51.159
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And then a few minutes later, flap-flop-flop-flop-flop, stay the same.

946
01:21:51.920 --> 01:21:53.969
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And that is the clock.

947
01:21:55.000 --> 01:21:57.330
Eric Rosenbaum: That is very strange, I love it.

948
01:22:00.120 --> 01:22:04.330
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): So, back to Lord Endless.

949
01:22:05.760 --> 01:22:11.629
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I think he's just said that there is an exit up the road, and you all have fallen ominously silent.

950
01:22:13.920 --> 01:22:18.369
Tim Sackton: So, I will ask… so he said there's an excerpt where I was saying.

951
01:22:18.850 --> 01:22:27.550
Tim Sackton: The woman was going there. And… He glances at the clock.

952
01:22:28.690 --> 01:22:39.489
Tim Sackton: And Char will say, char's not great at subtlety, so he's trying to go for, like…

953
01:22:40.330 --> 01:22:51.359
Tim Sackton: a hinting connection, to the clock, like, trying to, like, suddenly lead the conversation that way, but I think now he's sort of on shaky ground, and it comes out as…

954
01:22:51.830 --> 01:22:54.619
Tim Sackton: so, the clock?

955
01:22:57.830 --> 01:23:01.890
Tim Sackton: Something about the clock and her? What was up with that?

956
01:23:04.170 --> 01:23:11.750
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): if his face was blank before, it is utterly blank in response to that.

957
01:23:16.510 --> 01:23:22.129
Tim Sackton: Charles, like, glances over his shoulder at the two bars. It's like, okay, tag team time.

958
01:23:22.930 --> 01:23:33.220
Eric Rosenbaum: Wait, I think what my friend's trying to say is, could you help us just read the clock and tell what time it is? It's an amazing device. Never seen one like that before.

959
01:23:34.570 --> 01:23:40.300
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The, the badger butler gives a very gentle…

960
01:23:40.410 --> 01:23:47.990
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): nudge on Lord Ending's leg, and gestures with his chin in the direction of the,

961
01:23:48.080 --> 01:24:01.830
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): porch where the Rakshasa's sitting, which you can't see from here, because there are several walls in the way, but Lord Ending's head snaps in that direction, as if he is making eye contact with the Rakshasa through the walls.

962
01:24:01.830 --> 01:24:02.860
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And…

963
01:24:03.590 --> 01:24:12.350
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You see from the corner of your eye the slightest slump to his shoulders, as he guesses, maybe, what unfolded, and he says.

964
01:24:12.350 --> 01:24:20.409
Audio shared by David S. Kong: So, sorry, wait, not to interrupt, but just to clarify, we saw… we heard the clock cham something.

965
01:24:20.410 --> 01:24:23.560
Tim Sackton: And then we saw immediately after it chimed that.

966
01:24:24.650 --> 01:24:26.200
Kate Sackton: The Lord of the woman.

967
01:24:26.760 --> 01:24:27.280
Tim Sackton: the word.

968
01:24:27.660 --> 01:24:47.600
Audio shared by David S. Kong: That's exactly right. You heard it chime zero, and then that is immediately when he called someone over, and it's… I think you're not wrong in putting those things together. You see his shoulder slump an infinitesimally small degree, and he says, with a bit of wistfulness in the voice, so…

969
01:24:49.290 --> 01:24:52.359
Audio shared by David S. Kong: You spoke to the Rakshasa, anyways.

970
01:24:52.470 --> 01:24:54.199
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I think he figured it out.

971
01:24:54.420 --> 01:24:56.170
Audio shared by David S. Kong: From the other guests?

972
01:24:56.270 --> 01:24:58.649
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The ones that used to be here anyways?

973
01:24:59.730 --> 01:25:00.940
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yes.

974
01:25:01.100 --> 01:25:02.140
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Indeed.

975
01:25:03.070 --> 01:25:04.480
David S. Kong: What's a Rakshasa?

976
01:25:06.170 --> 01:25:08.090
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The, Tiger…

977
01:25:08.400 --> 01:25:14.260
David S. Kong: Kato's asking, because nobody told them that anybody spoke to a tiger. He was asking everybody what happened, what happened, nobody was like.

978
01:25:14.260 --> 01:25:14.879
Eric Rosenbaum: Oh, right.

979
01:25:14.880 --> 01:25:15.310
David S. Kong: I tell you.

980
01:25:15.310 --> 01:25:15.800
Kate Sackton: Alright.

981
01:25:15.800 --> 01:25:16.590
Mike Sackton: That's true.

982
01:25:16.590 --> 01:25:18.499
David S. Kong: I was like, what's… what's a Rakshasa?

983
01:25:18.950 --> 01:25:20.100
Eric Rosenbaum: Well.

984
01:25:20.890 --> 01:25:21.500
Kate Sackton: Another guest.

985
01:25:21.500 --> 01:25:23.760
Mike Sackton: Very good question. What is a web, Sasha?

986
01:25:25.390 --> 01:25:26.860
Mike Sackton: Edgek mispronounces it.

987
01:25:27.480 --> 01:25:32.450
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Lord Ending sort of looks away,

988
01:25:32.530 --> 01:25:51.019
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): covering for the embarrassment that he feels for his guests not knowing this. And instead, his badger butler pipes up and says, the mortal, the, the, the, with the pipe, the tiger, the, the mortal, on the porch.

989
01:25:51.240 --> 01:25:53.090
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The man who is a tiger.

990
01:25:53.970 --> 01:25:56.540
David S. Kong: Oh, I did not have the pleasure of meeting the Tiger Man.

991
01:25:56.920 --> 01:26:00.500
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): his… on the porch.

992
01:26:02.010 --> 01:26:03.359
Kate Sackton: On the porch he is!

993
01:26:04.090 --> 01:26:04.960
David S. Kong: on the porch.

994
01:26:06.670 --> 01:26:08.640
David S. Kong: Delightful.

995
01:26:09.020 --> 01:26:11.440
Tim Sackton: Wait, wait, wait, I'm still confused.

996
01:26:13.290 --> 01:26:15.550
Tim Sackton: The clock doesn't tell time.

997
01:26:17.660 --> 01:26:19.919
Tim Sackton: But… it chimes.

998
01:26:20.430 --> 01:26:22.170
Tim Sackton: And something happens.

999
01:26:24.720 --> 01:26:26.420
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Clock tells time.

1000
01:26:27.180 --> 01:26:30.500
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): When the clock strikes zero, it is time.

1001
01:26:35.460 --> 01:26:36.240
Mike Sackton: For dinner?

1002
01:26:36.240 --> 01:26:38.209
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): To show a guest home again.

1003
01:26:39.220 --> 01:26:41.250
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Through the neighbor's house up the road.

1004
01:26:42.860 --> 01:26:48.240
Tim Sackton: But we can… we don't have to wait for it to… Chime, do we?

1005
01:26:50.380 --> 01:26:53.370
Tim Sackton: Like, if we want to go home now, we can.

1006
01:26:58.000 --> 01:27:00.559
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yes… I don't…

1007
01:27:00.910 --> 01:27:01.710
Audio shared by David S. Kong: No.

1008
01:27:01.710 --> 01:27:02.479
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I don't know.

1009
01:27:03.900 --> 01:27:04.899
Mike Sackton: Do you like the clock?

1010
01:27:09.090 --> 01:27:11.880
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I dislike very deeply, having been tricked…

1011
01:27:12.020 --> 01:27:15.399
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): into an agreement I did not intend to make.

1012
01:27:16.400 --> 01:27:17.740
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I dislike…

1013
01:27:18.320 --> 01:27:18.900
Eric Rosenbaum: Hmm.

1014
01:27:18.900 --> 01:27:20.989
David S. Kong: Sorry, who said that? Was that… the Lord said that?

1015
01:27:20.990 --> 01:27:21.600
Kate Sackton: Yeah, yeah.

1016
01:27:22.100 --> 01:27:23.939
David S. Kong: Says, I dislike…

1017
01:27:24.360 --> 01:27:27.260
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Not being the lord of my own domain.

1018
01:27:28.240 --> 01:27:30.059
David S. Kong: What agreement? What happened?

1019
01:27:30.680 --> 01:27:31.980
Mike Sackton: That sounds horrible.

1020
01:27:34.370 --> 01:27:35.490
David S. Kong: Get a little poetry, that'.

1021
01:27:35.910 --> 01:27:40.600
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): What I presume the Rakshasa told you, or some of you, is that at the height of the party.

1022
01:27:41.990 --> 01:27:44.780
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): When things had really gotten going.

1023
01:27:47.110 --> 01:27:49.020
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Oh, it was a beautiful thing.

1024
01:27:50.120 --> 01:27:51.279
David S. Kong: It's like, I wish I could have seen it.

1025
01:27:51.660 --> 01:27:53.120
David S. Kong: Like, very genuinely.

1026
01:27:54.480 --> 01:27:56.099
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The neighbors came.

1027
01:27:56.100 --> 01:27:59.829
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Now, this is not an ideal time to meet one's new neighbors.

1028
01:27:59.950 --> 01:28:00.550
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Ugh.

1029
01:28:00.550 --> 01:28:00.890
David S. Kong: worse.

1030
01:28:01.660 --> 01:28:10.210
Audio shared by David S. Kong: But that is the time that they chose to come, all of them. Many of them. And the badger just shakes his head, sort of like in.

1031
01:28:10.240 --> 01:28:18.040
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): a sort of obsequiousness, like, like, ugh, how, who, how rude, how dare? How rude. Terrible. Muttering under his breath.

1032
01:28:19.480 --> 01:28:29.370
Audio shared by David S. Kong: They wanted a favor that I didn't want to give, and she tricked me into… Agreeing…

1033
01:28:30.270 --> 01:28:33.620
Audio shared by David S. Kong: To send my mortal guests home through that house.

1034
01:28:34.380 --> 01:28:41.900
Audio shared by David S. Kong: That whenever the clock strikes zero, I send one on up the road. And presumably, they get home, because certainly they don't return here.

1035
01:28:43.480 --> 01:28:51.910
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Nonetheless, I dislike being… Coerced into doing a thing that I did not choose myself to do.

1036
01:28:53.900 --> 01:28:54.500
David S. Kong: Fantastic.

1037
01:28:55.740 --> 01:28:56.410
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Whoa.

1038
01:28:58.460 --> 01:28:59.460
Mike Sackton: Your idea's probably better.

1039
01:29:01.710 --> 01:29:10.980
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Lord Endless Enly, I could not imagine… such a… Such actions of low integrity.

1040
01:29:12.560 --> 01:29:23.110
David S. Kong: Furthermore, a question, the mortals that are sent out, do you know if they even return home?

1041
01:29:25.530 --> 01:29:27.590
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It's not our business.

1042
01:29:28.160 --> 01:29:30.720
David S. Kong: laurement?

1043
01:29:30.920 --> 01:29:34.200
David S. Kong: And you were bound by this agreement?

1044
01:29:34.200 --> 01:29:37.389
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Indeed I am, though dearly I would like not to be.

1045
01:29:37.390 --> 01:29:43.050
David S. Kong: What could release you from this agreement?

1046
01:29:43.420 --> 01:29:44.370
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Isn't that awesome?

1047
01:29:45.380 --> 01:29:47.060
David S. Kong: You're going to allow home.

1048
01:29:47.800 --> 01:29:49.879
David S. Kong: We'll be sector with the other house?

1049
01:29:50.640 --> 01:29:51.789
David S. Kong: Okay, I must have been.

1050
01:29:52.340 --> 01:29:54.350
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Through certain portents.

1051
01:29:55.180 --> 01:30:00.180
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And certain signs… I have learned.

1052
01:30:02.190 --> 01:30:07.069
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): In the center of that house, There is a room.

1053
01:30:08.040 --> 01:30:16.060
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The bargainer, the wizard… called it the 27th room. I think she believed that would be poetic.

1054
01:30:17.040 --> 01:30:25.399
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): He says, with the deep sarcasm of someone who has a low opinion of another's poetry, The 27th room.

1055
01:30:26.350 --> 01:30:31.509
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Its walls… Are made of cold iron older than twilight.

1056
01:30:31.740 --> 01:30:32.260
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Love?

1057
01:30:32.510 --> 01:30:34.999
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): With a certain glass key.

1058
01:30:35.790 --> 01:30:36.350
Audio shared by David S. Kong: that holds.

1059
01:30:36.350 --> 01:30:38.230
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It's the last light of twilight.

1060
01:30:40.380 --> 01:30:45.270
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I have divined that if the key is returned to me and I break it.

1061
01:30:45.510 --> 01:30:47.840
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The bargain will be undone.

1062
01:30:50.350 --> 01:30:52.909
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And if you were to agree to do such a thing?

1063
01:30:54.730 --> 01:30:57.659
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Then I would agree to let the bargain go, and the key was returned to me.

1064
01:30:58.990 --> 01:30:59.780
David S. Kong: Then where's the key?

1065
01:31:01.450 --> 01:31:02.120
Audio shared by David S. Kong: -Oh.

1066
01:31:03.060 --> 01:31:04.880
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): In the lock of the 27th room.

1067
01:31:08.550 --> 01:31:10.399
David S. Kong: Have you sent anyone there to retrieve it?

1068
01:31:13.730 --> 01:31:14.990
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): No…

1069
01:31:16.720 --> 01:31:18.269
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Wait, why not?

1070
01:31:22.830 --> 01:31:24.470
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I've always believed…

1071
01:31:27.580 --> 01:31:30.139
Audio shared by David S. Kong: That someone CAN'T go in.

1072
01:31:30.400 --> 01:31:36.129
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Until the clock chimes zero, although I confess your question has taken me off guard, because perhaps you could.

1073
01:31:39.490 --> 01:31:43.629
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And when the clock chimes at zero, I am obliged.

1074
01:31:44.450 --> 01:31:46.470
Audio shared by David S. Kong: To send a mortal guest through.

1075
01:31:46.470 --> 01:31:46.870
Eric Rosenbaum: Curtain.

1076
01:31:49.280 --> 01:31:50.769
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Caught in a bind that…

1077
01:31:51.150 --> 01:31:56.719
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Unless one of my guests, as you do, approached me to ask to do such a thing.

1078
01:31:57.300 --> 01:32:02.000
Audio shared by David S. Kong: I couldn't task them to do it, because to task them to do it would be to…

1079
01:32:02.710 --> 01:32:04.449
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Forsake the task which I swore to do.

1080
01:32:05.190 --> 01:32:05.930
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Ugh.

1081
01:32:06.460 --> 01:32:07.390
Audio shared by David S. Kong: A conundrum.

1082
01:32:10.310 --> 01:32:13.020
Audio shared by David S. Kong: That weird. So… Idea.

1083
01:32:15.330 --> 01:32:16.089
Audio shared by David S. Kong: What was that?

1084
01:32:16.300 --> 01:32:20.579
Kate Sackton: I'm so glad we approached with the idea, because it does seem unworthy activity.

1085
01:32:24.510 --> 01:32:29.310
Audio shared by David S. Kong: One other clarifying question… And also for your Lord's awareness.

1086
01:32:30.490 --> 01:32:32.500
Audio shared by David S. Kong: The mortals sent down the road?

1087
01:32:33.110 --> 01:32:37.859
David S. Kong: Are you aware of… Bodies on the road?

1088
01:32:38.220 --> 01:32:39.170
David S. Kong: As well?

1089
01:32:41.420 --> 01:32:44.590
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I confess I have not left my grounds since the party began.

1090
01:32:45.230 --> 01:32:46.389
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): At Twilight.

1091
01:32:47.050 --> 01:32:52.230
David S. Kong: Well, for your Lord's awareness, as we traveled to come to the party.

1092
01:32:52.810 --> 01:32:58.020
David S. Kong: We found some pretty gnarly sights. Some… kind of?

1093
01:32:58.130 --> 01:32:59.150
David S. Kong: I don't know.

1094
01:32:59.520 --> 01:33:03.540
David S. Kong: Decapitated, mutilated bodies, on the road?

1095
01:33:04.610 --> 01:33:08.739
David S. Kong: And… Again, we don't know where they came from.

1096
01:33:10.110 --> 01:33:13.620
David S. Kong: We… one hypothesis is that

1097
01:33:13.940 --> 01:33:21.450
David S. Kong: They came from the party, and never made it to the house in question, and somehow their heads were removed.

1098
01:33:21.810 --> 01:33:23.289
David S. Kong: That's one possibility.

1099
01:33:23.860 --> 01:33:25.720
David S. Kong: But, we actually don't know.

1100
01:33:25.950 --> 01:33:28.460
David S. Kong: And I don't know if that information…

1101
01:33:28.970 --> 01:33:34.219
David S. Kong: Disturbs you, raises more questions, answers some questions, but…

1102
01:33:34.530 --> 01:33:39.720
David S. Kong: I share with your Lord these facts that we have observed upon entry of your fine manner.

1103
01:33:42.560 --> 01:33:44.020
David S. Kong: I'm wrong, Lisa.

1104
01:33:44.990 --> 01:33:46.150
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I am the Lord.

1105
01:33:46.530 --> 01:33:49.480
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Of an endlessly ending party.

1106
01:33:51.150 --> 01:33:57.429
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): My domain… And my responsibility to my guests ceases

1107
01:33:57.750 --> 01:34:02.020
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): At the gate, just as it does where the river flows around the bend.

1108
01:34:02.820 --> 01:34:04.549
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): If there are bodies on the road.

1109
01:34:05.300 --> 01:34:06.780
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): What has it to do with me?

1110
01:34:06.780 --> 01:34:07.400
David S. Kong: button.

1111
01:34:07.890 --> 01:34:09.089
David S. Kong: In my vocal.

1112
01:34:09.990 --> 01:34:12.709
David S. Kong: Only in so much as it relates to your agreement.

1113
01:34:14.950 --> 01:34:21.879
David S. Kong: In other words, if these were the mortals being released from your house, Going to your neighbor's house.

1114
01:34:22.340 --> 01:34:25.010
David S. Kong: And they never made it there to go home.

