03:09:09.470 --> 03:09:09.999
David S. Kong: Was it pushing?

2526
03:09:11.330 --> 03:09:11.880
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Linda?

2527
03:09:11.880 --> 03:09:12.600
Mike Sackton: No doubt.

2528
03:09:12.740 --> 03:09:14.790
Mike Sackton: Did anybody know what a drag car had been?

2529
03:09:15.490 --> 03:09:19.669
Kate Sackton: Do we know the rough… rough year range age-ish that…

2530
03:09:19.960 --> 03:09:21.309
David S. Kong: That.

2531
03:09:21.710 --> 03:09:23.550
Kate Sackton: the Joint Korean Empire ended.

2532
03:09:23.550 --> 03:09:25.219
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Sometime in the 1000s.

2533
03:09:25.500 --> 03:09:28.110
Kate Sackton: I mean, I can roll an arcana, right?

2534
03:09:28.320 --> 03:09:31.720
Tim Sackton: You probably know, you're profici- you have expertise in history.

2535
03:09:32.860 --> 03:09:36.979
Mike Sackton: Yeah, you would definitely know if you have any… I mean, it's a pretty meaningful year.

2536
03:09:37.300 --> 03:09:39.830
Kate Sackton: Plus 6 to my history, yes. I probably don't.

2537
03:09:39.830 --> 03:09:41.600
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Momentous year. 1059.

2538
03:09:41.990 --> 03:09:42.980
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): wanted it.

2539
03:09:43.100 --> 03:09:45.670
Kate Sackton: That's… I know that year. I say that year.

2540
03:09:48.260 --> 03:09:51.340
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I cannot believe she was right. I…

2541
03:09:51.610 --> 03:09:53.630
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): I don't know how she called it.

2542
03:09:54.370 --> 03:09:55.070
David S. Kong: What'd she say?

2543
03:09:55.070 --> 03:09:56.279
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): It's ridiculous.

2544
03:09:56.520 --> 03:09:58.090
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): That's ridiculous.

2545
03:09:59.110 --> 03:10:04.360
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Oh my god, everyone I have ever known is dead. Oh my god. Oh my god.

2546
03:10:04.810 --> 03:10:07.159
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): People still speak Drancorin, though, right?

2547
03:10:09.280 --> 03:10:10.840
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Oh, my God.

2548
03:10:10.840 --> 03:10:11.660
Mike Sackton: No?

2549
03:10:15.110 --> 03:10:16.260
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Oh…

2550
03:10:19.750 --> 03:10:20.600
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Wow.

2551
03:10:22.500 --> 03:10:23.460
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Wow.

2552
03:10:26.360 --> 03:10:26.960
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Well…

2553
03:10:30.550 --> 03:10:34.889
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Onwards, then, I don't feel like I can wait much longer.

2554
03:10:36.090 --> 03:10:36.850
Kate Sackton: Go ahead!

2555
03:10:37.030 --> 03:10:38.939
Kate Sackton: Either way, you've been there before.

2556
03:10:42.640 --> 03:10:43.570
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Yeah.

2557
03:10:46.390 --> 03:10:47.490
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Yeah.

2558
03:10:47.760 --> 03:10:49.310
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): But not inside.

2559
03:10:57.200 --> 03:11:00.950
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): You go out down the gate, And I think,

2560
03:11:01.650 --> 03:11:06.340
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Let me wrap just with a description of arriving at the… Doorway?

2561
03:11:08.720 --> 03:11:11.140
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Tim, will you put that background up for us?

2562
03:11:12.530 --> 03:11:14.169
Audio shared by David S. Kong: As you walk down the road.

2563
03:11:14.570 --> 03:11:20.050
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The land begins to fall away, down into a ravine on the left-hand side.

2564
03:11:20.120 --> 03:11:21.709
Audio shared by David S. Kong: the westward side.

2565
03:11:23.110 --> 03:11:27.649
Audio shared by David S. Kong: And in the…

2566
03:11:29.520 --> 03:11:36.239
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And then it branches off to the left, and the main road continues on to the north, but off to the west.

2567
03:11:36.340 --> 03:11:54.200
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): A footpath leads down this promontory which rises and which narrows the further out you go, until by the time you're nearer to the end of it, and see not a building, but just a single door sitting at the end of the path with nothing else around it.

2568
03:11:55.030 --> 03:12:02.550
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): There are cliffs on all sides, falling away to a darkness at the bottom, in which you cannot discern.

2569
03:12:02.550 --> 03:12:03.630
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Anything.

2570
03:12:03.630 --> 03:12:09.600
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Deep, deep in the shadow, where even the last light of twilight can't reach.

2571
03:12:14.030 --> 03:12:18.269
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): As you stand there, In front of the door.

2572
03:12:19.880 --> 03:12:32.749
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Each of you glancing to the other, knowing that you're going to walk through it. In fact, knowing that you already have, that you wouldn't have been able to leave the party unless you already had in the future.

2573
03:12:33.460 --> 03:12:34.330
Eric Rosenbaum: Hmm.

2574
03:12:34.970 --> 03:12:38.080
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): The camera cuts away from the party.

2575
03:12:38.460 --> 03:12:44.390
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): back to the Lord of… The endlessly ending.

2576
03:12:45.760 --> 03:12:48.180
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Standing by himself.

2577
03:12:49.460 --> 03:12:56.840
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Looking away over the lawns, At the party which is just coming apart.

2578
03:12:57.380 --> 03:13:01.150
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Knowing that the best of it is behind him already.

2579
03:13:02.260 --> 03:13:10.250
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And he speaks into the silence, something that you all don't hear, but the camera does, so I'll share it with you.

2580
03:13:14.680 --> 03:13:22.839
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): As if to you, though, because the camera cuts back over your faces as he's speaking this underneath.

2581
03:13:23.440 --> 03:13:26.820
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Shadow walks beside you in the gloaming.

2582
03:13:27.360 --> 03:13:30.300
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Whispering a name that you forgot to fear.

2583
03:13:30.310 --> 03:13:36.720
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Bring its key, I'll break my oath, avowing you'll watch this heavy contract disappear.

2584
03:13:37.490 --> 03:13:44.539
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Where floorboards cry beneath a hidden weight of ancient seed or grown long pruned on mist.

2585
03:13:44.980 --> 03:13:51.709
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Spin the rusted wheels of that weary place, and keep us all far from its bright abyss.

2586
03:13:52.580 --> 03:13:58.890
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Unveil the phantom shape I cannot trace, the quiet path a turning labyrinth weaves.

2587
03:13:59.350 --> 03:14:06.070
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Unlock the stranger prisoned in that place and strip the shroud your waking mind believes.

2588
03:14:07.130 --> 03:14:10.409
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): So take the secret path I cannot see.

2589
03:14:10.960 --> 03:14:12.419
Audio shared by David S. Kong: Bring back the key.

2590
03:14:12.610 --> 03:14:14.500
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): And finally set me free.

2591
03:14:17.790 --> 03:14:19.390
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): They too black.

2592
03:14:22.890 --> 03:14:23.910
Mike Sackton: cavity?

2593
03:14:26.020 --> 03:14:30.479
Tim Sackton: Just out of curiosity, where is my owl?

2594
03:14:30.890 --> 03:14:31.900
Eric Rosenbaum: Yeah, that was fun.

2595
03:14:31.900 --> 03:14:33.420
Kate Sackton: wondering that.

2596
03:14:35.220 --> 03:14:41.800
Rev. David Schwartz (he/him): Oh man, because it is too good to pass up, that owl is 100% perched on top of the doorframe right now.

2597
03:14:41.800 --> 03:14:42.630
Eric Rosenbaum: Nice.

2598
03:14:49.620 --> 03:14:50.580
Tim Sackton: Okay.

